            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Nice! Is this at the limit for particles, or can you shrink them and have, say, 10x as many?"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "two-minute-week",
    "channel_id": "C0120A3L30R"
  },
  {
    "text": "Probably, I haven't tried, but the machine wasn't under any strain doing this and recording it.  I could increase the granularity of the sensor too.  The idea is to show this as 'here's roughly how it works in the real world', but then 'here's how we do it when ray-tracing, by firing the particles in reverse from the camera.\n\nThe 'sister' demo, is the 3D version, also in Rust.  My plan here is to do a series where I gradually build up to something more realistic; with this as the most basic starting point....",
