    "text": "Following the <https://futureofcoding.slack.com/archives/C01932BJGE8/p1711916139930599|conversation here> I decided to experiment with a \"Month of Future of Coding Past\".\n\nEvery week I will dump from tinyletter and re upload one month of the <https://newsletter.futureofcoding.org/|Future of Coding Newsletter> and publish it as a message here, that way we can all go over past conversations and links and I have a reason and rhythm to make them available again.\n\nA month re uploaded per week will allow me to catch up faster than \"realtime\" but still at a pace I can probably keep.\n\nHere's the first edition, the first two newsletters I have in my email (January 2020):\n\n• <https://newsletter.futureofcoding.org/posts/future-of-coding-weekly-202001-week-3/|Future of Coding Weekly 2020/01 Week 3>\n• <https://newsletter.futureofcoding.org/posts/future-of-coding-weekly-202001-week-4/|Future of Coding Weekly 2020/01 Week 4>",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
